fields.description: The user console does not allow deregistration of images. If a user is allowed to register a snapshot as an image they should be allowed to deregister it. If the image cannot be deregistered then the snapshot cannot be deleted.
fields.summary: User Console: Unable to register/deregister images from images page

comments.body: Snapshot's registration was added as bonus to 3.2, that is why it is not fully cooked.
Will need a workaround using the CLI to delete snapshots
We could potentially implement this small change to the GUI for "delete snapshots" that will also deregister the image. Vic says there's resources to test this. See attached file for possible design.

On Vic's setup : 192.168.51.133, there are two zones . Deleting the snapshot is suppose to also remove the image but the deletion failed, and image and snapshot remained registered.

error in pop-up:

snap-8CA33C3B: Snapshot snap-8CA33C3B is in use, deletion not permitted.

NOTE: This likely works in single zone setup.
Image remains after snapshot deletion failed.
Failed on 192.168.51.133 in a two zone setup. Likely works in a single zone.

There are no additional actions : 
[ check  delete image ]  presented .
John used the system that does not have fix, so it obviously failed. Passing back to Jonh.
System updated to Monday build. Test passed
Passed. Image deleted when snap shot was deleted.

worklogs.comment: Passed. Image deleted when snap shot was deleted.
